    "title": "Defining and converting units and quantities"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKUnit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " class provides the representation for a single unit. It supports a wide range of metric and imperial units, as well as both simple and complex units. A simple unit represents a single measurement, such as meters, pounds, or seconds. A complex unit combines one or more simple units using mathematical operations, such as meters per second (m/s) or pounds per square foot (lb/ft2).",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In addition to convenience methods for creating all the simple units supported by HealthKit, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKUnit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " provides the mathematical operations needed to build complex units. You can also create complex units directly using properly formatted unit strings.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more information on units, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKUnit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKQuantity",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " class stores a value for a given unit. You can then request the value in any compatible units, letting your app easily translate values between units.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more information on quantities, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKQuantity",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/measurementformatter",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to localize quantities such as length, mass, and energy. For other quantities, you need to perform the conversions and localize the data yourself.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
